\f + \fr 6:2\ft Mountains, where idols were chiefly adored. Here their votaries find death. (Worthington) --- Israel, including all God's people, as the sacred writers make no distinction (Calmet) after the destruction of Samaria.\f*
\f + \fr 6:4\ft Idols. Protestant marginal note, "sun-images," as [in] ver. 6. The sun was much worshipped, Ezechiel 8:16. (Haydock)\f*
\f + \fr 6:5\ft Bones. The Chaldeans violated the tombs, Baruch 2:24., and Jeremias 8:1. (Calmet)\f*
\f + \fr 6:8\ft Some. Providence still preserves some faithful or penitent souls. (Worthington)\f*
\f + \fr 6:9\ft Broken. Adversity has made them repent.\f*
\f + \fr 6:11\ft Foot, through indignation or pity. (Calmet)\f*
\f + \fr 6:14\ft From, or, "more than," (Haydock) as Hebrew may signify. Deblatha was in the land of Moab, Numbers 33:46. (Calmet)\f*
